      <body>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83209">
             <p><lb n="1"/>sidha <space unit="character" quantity="1"/> bhagavā <space unit="character" quantity="1"/> samasabudho kausadho <space unit="character" quantity="1"/> Upāsakena vākāṭicāna <space unit="character" quantity="1"/> visākhena <space unit="character" quantity="1"/> saputakena kāripit<unclear>o</unclear></p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
             <listApp>
                 <app loc="1">
                     <lem>kausadho</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01">kosadho</rdg>
                     <note>See also <bibl><ptr target="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"/><citedRange unit="page">14</citedRange></bibl>: <quote>[E]ven the name of the Buddha Kakosa(ṁ)dho is miswritten as Kosadho</quote>. The reading <foreign>kausadho</foreign> is certain, since the additional loop to the right of the vocalic marker <foreign>-o</foreign> is clearly visible. This may be understood as an alternative way to render <foreign>kaUsadho</foreign>, corresponding to Buddhist Sanskrit <foreign xml:lang="san-Latn">krakutsanda</foreign>. See also the Gāndharī name <foreign>Kosudha</foreign>, coexisting alongside <foreign>Kosuda</foreign> and <foreign>Kravasudha</foreign> in in the Library of Congress scroll of the <foreign>Bahubudhagasutra</foreign>. See <bibl><ptr target="bib:Tournier2017_01"/><citedRange unit="page">200</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="bib:Salomon2018_01"/><citedRange unit="page">397-398</citedRange><citedRange unit="note">374</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                 </app>
             </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="part:vito">
             <p>Success! The Bhagavant, Buddha Kausudha (Skt. Krakutsanda), commissioned by the <foreign>upāsaka</foreign> Visāgha (Skt. Viśākha) of the Vāgāḍhica family, together with his son<supplied reason="subaudible">s</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
